00:34:32.532 --> 00:34:34.099
What if it's too late?

543
00:34:37.103 --> 00:34:40.373
Let's eat
pomegranates...


544
00:34:40.440 --> 00:34:43.409
Till our hands
turn red and...


545
00:34:43.477 --> 00:34:44.977
And all we can
think about


546
00:34:45.044 --> 00:34:46.846
Is getting
the juice off.


547
00:34:46.913 --> 00:34:48.447
[giggles]

548
00:34:49.850 --> 00:34:51.283
Hmm...

549
00:34:58.992 --> 00:35:00.893
Mo!

550
00:35:00.961 --> 00:35:02.561
Mo, let's get
our fortunes told.


551
00:35:04.180 --> 00:35:05.748
Not by her.

552
00:35:05.815 --> 00:35:06.949
Come on, now.

553
00:35:07.150 --> 00:35:08.750
You said you wanted
to cheer me up. Come on.


554
00:35:08.818 --> 00:35:10.870
Roz, that woman couldn't
predict heat in August.


555
00:35:10.937 --> 00:35:12.071
Mozelle Batiste...

556
00:35:12.139 --> 00:35:14.073
If I didn't know you
better, I'd say you had


557
00:35:14.141 --> 00:35:15.674
A case of professional
jealousy.


558
00:35:15.742 --> 00:35:18.310
Roz, I am
a psychic counselor.


559
00:35:18.378 --> 00:35:20.379
Elzora's a sideshow
attraction.


560
00:35:20.446 --> 00:35:21.947
Well, then there's
nothing to be afraid of.


561
00:35:22.015 --> 00:35:22.882
Come on.

562
00:35:26.703 --> 00:35:28.620
Which one first?

563
00:35:28.789 --> 00:35:32.274
Well...

564
00:35:32.341 --> 00:35:35.744
My--my sister-in-law is
something of a skeptic.


565
00:35:35.812 --> 00:35:38.781
But I'd very much
like my fortune told.


566
00:35:40.450 --> 00:35:41.350
Sit down.

567
00:35:52.262 --> 00:35:53.813
Empty it.

568
00:36:08.328 --> 00:36:09.995
You're in pain,
my daughter.


569
00:36:11.465 --> 00:36:12.932
Yes.

570
00:36:12.999 --> 00:36:15.868
There is an end
to your problem...


571
00:36:15.936 --> 00:36:19.505
Though not one
you imagined.


572
00:36:22.542 --> 00:36:24.343
Stay quiet.

573
00:36:24.410 --> 00:36:26.378
And wait.

574
00:36:26.446 --> 00:36:28.581
Wait?

575
00:36:28.648 --> 00:36:31.416
Sometimes a soldier
fall on his own sword.


576
00:36:33.803 --> 00:36:35.687
In 3 years time...

577
00:36:35.755 --> 00:36:37.923
You will be happy
again.


578
00:36:39.860 --> 00:36:41.126
3 years?

579
00:36:44.597 --> 00:36:46.365
Look to your children.

580
00:36:51.371 --> 00:36:52.437
Dollar.

581
00:36:58.078 --> 00:36:59.745
That's it?

582
00:36:59.812 --> 00:37:02.948
Just wait 3 years,
and everything will be fine?


583
00:37:03.016 --> 00:37:05.751
Look to your children.

584
00:37:07.820 --> 00:37:09.021
Well...

585
00:37:12.359 --> 00:37:15.227
Thank you.

586
00:37:15.295 --> 00:37:18.197
I feel most enlightened.

587
00:37:18.265 --> 00:37:20.132
Good afternoon.

588
00:37:22.969 --> 00:37:24.370
You were right.
Come on.


589
00:37:24.437 --> 00:37:25.905
Wait.

590
00:37:47.093 --> 00:37:50.695
Some things are
better left unsaid.


591
00:37:50.763 --> 00:37:53.966
I paid you a dollar,
old woman.


592
00:37:54.034 --> 00:37:56.701
Now tell my fortune.

593
00:37:56.769 --> 00:37:58.703
I don't need
no cat bones


594
00:37:58.771 --> 00:38:01.407
To tell your fortune,
Mozelle Batiste.


595
00:38:01.474 --> 00:38:03.809
You are a curse.

596
00:38:03.876 --> 00:38:05.644
The black widow.

597
00:38:05.711 --> 00:38:08.513
Next man who marries you
is a dead man,


598
00:38:08.581 --> 00:38:10.749
Like the others.

599
00:38:10.817 --> 00:38:13.819
Always be that way.

600
00:38:13.886 --> 00:38:16.655
[cursing in Creole]

601
00:38:19.975 --> 00:38:23.512
You're a horrid
old lying witch!


602
00:38:26.382 --> 00:38:28.267
Wait a minute!

603
00:38:28.335 --> 00:38:29.201
Mozelle!

604
00:38:39.545 --> 00:38:41.913
For Heaven's sake,
what did she say?


605
00:38:41.982 --> 00:38:44.549
It's all right.
It's just the heat.


606
00:38:44.617 --> 00:38:46.352
I need to catch my--

607
00:38:46.419 --> 00:38:47.886
Mo, come on.
Let's not be in the street.


608
00:38:58.047 --> 00:38:59.548
[screaming]

609
00:39:02.619 --> 00:39:04.453
Mo?

610
00:39:04.520 --> 00:39:06.020
Mo?

611
00:39:08.157 --> 00:39:09.190
It's dead.

612
00:39:09.259 --> 00:39:11.526
Are you sure?

613
00:39:11.594 --> 00:39:14.396
It's not moving,
is it?


614
00:39:14.464 --> 00:39:16.632
Maybe it's just sick.

615
00:39:17.900 --> 00:39:21.136
It's dead,
you little chicken.


616
00:39:27.076 --> 00:39:30.812
Aah!
Aah!


617
00:39:30.880 --> 00:39:32.414
[screaming]

618
00:39:39.722 --> 00:39:41.856
Oh, Cisely!

619
00:39:41.924 --> 00:39:42.791
Thank heavens!

620
00:39:44.860 --> 00:39:47.128
Where are Eve
and Poe?


621
00:39:47.196 --> 00:39:48.997
Mama, I don't know.

622
00:39:49.064 --> 00:39:50.465
[Eve and Poe
screaming]


623
00:39:50.533 --> 00:39:51.466
Oh, Lord.

624
00:39:51.534 --> 00:39:53.769
[Eve and Poe screaming]

625
00:39:56.005 --> 00:39:57.439
Are you all right?

626
00:39:57.507 --> 00:40:00.942
Are you all right?

627
00:40:01.010 --> 00:40:04.145
No, just go. Git.
Go ahead. Come on!


628
00:40:04.213 --> 00:40:07.949
Just go! Don't ask me,
just git!


629
00:40:11.954 --> 00:40:12.987
Louis: You're telling me

630
00:40:13.055 --> 00:40:14.122
You're going to lock
these kids up in the house


631
00:40:14.324 --> 00:40:15.507
For the rest of the Summer

632
00:40:15.575 --> 00:40:17.475
'cause of something that
old fortune-teller told you?


633
00:40:17.543 --> 00:40:20.278
She just kept saying,
"look to your children."


634
00:40:20.346 --> 00:40:22.915
And no sooner do we leave
than Mozelle has this vision


635
00:40:22.982 --> 00:40:24.149
Of a child getting hit.

636
00:40:24.217 --> 00:40:25.650
[laughs]

637
00:40:25.719 --> 00:40:27.485
Roz, you know
I love my sister,


638
00:40:27.553 --> 00:40:28.486
But she's not unfamiliar

639
00:40:28.554 --> 00:40:30.155
With the inside
of a mental hospital.


640
00:40:30.223 --> 00:40:32.758
Louis, not in front
of the children.


641
00:40:32.826 --> 00:40:33.792
Louis: They know.

642
00:40:33.860 --> 00:40:34.827
Of course we know.

643
00:40:34.894 --> 00:40:36.195
Know what?

644
00:40:36.262 --> 00:40:37.495
Aunt Mozelle's crazy.

645
00:40:37.563 --> 00:40:38.630
She is not!

646
00:40:38.698 --> 00:40:41.366
She knows things.
People trust her.


647
00:40:41.434 --> 00:40:42.367
Louis: Sweetheart,

648
00:40:42.435 --> 00:40:43.568
Your aunt Mozelle’s
a little eccentric.


649
00:40:43.636 --> 00:40:45.070
That fortune-telling's
something we let her do


650
00:40:45.138 --> 00:40:46.071
To keep her
out of trouble.


651
00:40:46.139 --> 00:40:47.773
She may be crazy,

652
00:40:47.841 --> 00:40:50.809
But them visions
always come true.


653
00:40:50.877 --> 00:40:53.145
Anyway...

654
00:40:53.213 --> 00:40:55.413
I've made up my mind.

655
00:40:55.481 --> 00:40:57.082
They're staying
in the house.


656
00:40:57.150 --> 00:40:58.817
Till when?

657
00:41:00.253 --> 00:41:01.620
Well, I don't know.

658
00:41:01.687 --> 00:41:03.421
Till Mozelle says
it's safe.


659
00:41:03.489 --> 00:41:05.124
Louis: I can't believe
I'm hearing this.


660
00:41:05.191 --> 00:41:08.426
What if we promise
not to play in traffic?


661
00:41:08.494 --> 00:41:10.495
Don't use that tone of voice
with me, Cisely Batiste.


662
00:41:10.563 --> 00:41:12.864
And don't be rolling
your eyes at your father


663
00:41:12.932 --> 00:41:13.948
Behind my back.

664
00:41:14.017 --> 00:41:15.484
You're looking
right at us, mama.


665
00:41:15.551 --> 00:41:16.851
Nothing ever happens
behind your back.


666
00:41:16.919 --> 00:41:19.354
Don't talk back
to your mother, young lady!


667
00:41:19.422 --> 00:41:21.423
You're not too big
to beat.


668
00:41:21.491 --> 00:41:22.790
Don't threaten
my daughter, mama.


669
00:41:22.858 --> 00:41:24.325
You let her threaten me.

670
00:41:27.080 --> 00:41:30.415
When I was growing up,
children did not participate


671
00:41:30.483 --> 00:41:32.384
In the conversation
of adults.


672
00:41:33.686 --> 00:41:35.154
You can let them kids

673
00:41:35.221 --> 00:41:36.889
Back-talk and run wild
if you want to.


674
00:41:36.956 --> 00:41:38.773
You won't hear
another word out of me.


675
00:41:40.276 --> 00:41:41.510
In my day,

676
00:41:41.577 --> 00:41:45.147
We were thankful
for signs and warnings.


677
00:41:45.214 --> 00:41:47.416
Go on and let
the little hooligans


678
00:41:47.483 --> 00:41:48.400
Get runned over.

679
00:41:48.467 --> 00:41:51.336
<i>Ca va plus tranquille</i>
<i>autour d'ici.</i>


680
00:41:51.404 --> 00:41:53.839
It will be much quieter
around here.


681
00:41:59.712 --> 00:42:01.079
I want to thank you all

682
00:42:01.147 --> 00:42:02.714
For the delightful
family chat.


683
00:42:02.782 --> 00:42:04.449
I have patients to see.

684
00:42:04.517 --> 00:42:05.650
Louis...

685
00:42:05.718 --> 00:42:08.187
It's Sunday.

686
00:42:08.254 --> 00:42:09.988
When you find
a way to put sickness


687
00:42:10.056 --> 00:42:11.824
On a 8-hour, 5-day schedule,
you let me know.


688
00:42:11.891 --> 00:42:13.425
Well, what's wrong with them
they can't wait a day?


689
00:42:13.492 --> 00:42:16.094
Are you two
going to fight?


690
00:42:16.162 --> 00:42:19.664
Some sickness is hard
to put a finger on.


691
00:42:23.803 --> 00:42:26.171
I'll be back
soon as I can.


692
00:42:29.242 --> 00:42:32.044
Which one of your patients
you going to see, Louis?


693
00:42:34.380 --> 00:42:36.949
Woman, go get your palm read
and let me do my work.


694
00:42:50.813 --> 00:42:52.213
You love your daddy,
baby?


695
00:42:52.281 --> 00:42:53.582
You know I do.

696
00:42:53.649 --> 00:42:55.316
That's all I need.

697
00:43:03.960 --> 00:43:05.560
Excuse me, darling.

698
00:43:08.898 --> 00:43:10.966
Don't you think you're
being a little immature?


699
00:43:13.803 --> 00:43:15.937
I beg your pardon?

700
00:43:16.005 --> 00:43:17.939
Keeping us in the house

701
00:43:18.007 --> 00:43:19.641
'cause aunt Mozelle’s
seeing things


702
00:43:19.709 --> 00:43:22.210
And not wanting daddy
to go to work.


703
00:43:22.277 --> 00:43:24.278
What's wrong with you?

704
00:43:34.123 --> 00:43:35.390
If you're lucky,

705
00:43:35.458 --> 00:43:37.359
You might live long
enough to one day have


706
00:43:37.426 --> 00:43:39.027
A husband and children
of your own,


707
00:43:39.094 --> 00:43:41.429
But until then,
this is my house,


708
00:43:41.497 --> 00:43:42.464
And you will do
as I say.


709
00:43:42.532 --> 00:43:43.465
Do you understand?

710
00:43:44.833 --> 00:43:47.752
I said,
do you understand?


711
00:43:47.820 --> 00:43:49.721
Yes, ma'am.

712
00:43:52.691 --> 00:43:53.558
Good.

713
00:43:58.314 --> 00:44:01.916
No one leaves this house
until I say so.


714
00:44:20.219 --> 00:44:21.653
What man art thou,

715
00:44:21.721 --> 00:44:23.789
That thus bescreen'd
in night,


716
00:44:23.856 --> 00:44:26.090
So stumblest
on my counsel?


717
00:44:26.158 --> 00:44:27.526
By a name...

718
00:44:27.593 --> 00:44:30.729
I know not how
to tell thee who I am.


719
00:44:30.797 --> 00:44:33.832
My ring says that
I am king myself...


720
00:44:52.585 --> 00:44:54.319
[sighs]

721
00:45:03.529 --> 00:45:06.130
[sighs]

722
00:45:11.337 --> 00:45:13.405
What are you doing
in there?!


723
00:45:13.473 --> 00:45:15.874
Cisely: Go away!

724
00:45:58.785 --> 00:46:00.452
Aah!

725
00:46:00.520 --> 00:46:02.888
Ouch!

726
00:46:02.955 --> 00:46:04.890
God damn it.

727
00:46:04.957 --> 00:46:06.525
<i>Ferme to guele, hein!</i>

728
00:46:06.592 --> 00:46:07.992
Eve: I heard you.

729
00:46:08.060 --> 00:46:09.994
You said
"God damn it."


730
00:46:10.062 --> 00:46:11.329
Eve.

731
00:46:11.397 --> 00:46:13.498
You shouldn't be
sneaking up on people


732
00:46:13.566 --> 00:46:14.933
When they're swearing
to themselves.


733
00:46:15.000 --> 00:46:16.435
Does it hurt?

734
00:46:16.502 --> 00:46:17.636
What?

735
00:46:17.703 --> 00:46:19.170
Your finger, mother.

736
00:46:19.238 --> 00:46:23.341
Oh. No, not too much.

737
00:46:23.409 --> 00:46:25.276
You're gonna cut your finger
off one of these days.


738
00:46:25.344 --> 00:46:28.179
'tis not so deep
as a well,


739
00:46:28.247 --> 00:46:30.615
Nor so wide
as a church door,


740
00:46:30.683 --> 00:46:34.419
But 'tis enough,
'twill serve.


741
00:46:38.524 --> 00:46:40.024
<i>Romeo and Juliet.</i>

742
00:46:40.092 --> 00:46:41.292
[chopping]

743
00:46:41.360 --> 00:46:42.293
What?

744
00:46:42.361 --> 00:46:44.629
We read most
of the tragedies.


745
00:46:44.697 --> 00:46:47.131
We're starting on
the goddamn comedies.


746
00:46:47.199 --> 00:46:49.734
You are asking
to get hit.


747
00:46:49.802 --> 00:46:50.735
[Poe screaming]

748
00:46:50.803 --> 00:46:51.736
Baby!

749
00:46:51.804 --> 00:46:52.804
[Poe screaming]

750
00:46:52.872 --> 00:46:54.172
Lord have mercy.

751
00:46:54.239 --> 00:46:56.074
[Poe screaming]

752
00:46:56.141 --> 00:46:58.309
What happened, baby?

753
00:46:58.377 --> 00:46:59.344
You all right?

754
00:46:59.411 --> 00:47:01.680
Poe: Mama!

755
00:47:01.747 --> 00:47:02.647
Mama, where are you?!

756
00:47:02.715 --> 00:47:03.648
Hey, mo.

757
00:47:03.716 --> 00:47:05.383
Poe, are you all right?

758
00:47:05.451 --> 00:47:07.051
Look what I found
in the attic.


759
00:47:07.119 --> 00:47:09.588
A monopoly board
and Chinese checkers.


760
00:47:09.655 --> 00:47:10.856
Girl, you could find
the czar of Russia


761
00:47:10.923 --> 00:47:11.857
In that attic.

762
00:47:11.924 --> 00:47:13.992
I despise
Chinese checkers.


763
00:47:14.059 --> 00:47:15.494
Poe: I hate her!
I hate her!


764
00:47:15.561 --> 00:47:17.996
I wish she was dead!

765
00:47:18.063 --> 00:47:21.299
I feel like I walked into
the middle of a cyclone.


766
00:47:21.367 --> 00:47:24.002
Eve, what did you do
to your brother?


767
00:47:24.069 --> 00:47:25.670
I'm going to push him
out of a window


768
00:47:25.738 --> 00:47:27.138
If I don't get
out of this house.


769
00:47:27.206 --> 00:47:28.139
Eve!

770
00:47:28.207 --> 00:47:30.308
Cisely's been
in the goddamn bathtub


771
00:47:30.376 --> 00:47:32.744
For an hour,
you know that?


772
00:47:32.812 --> 00:47:34.980
She stayed in there

773
00:47:35.047 --> 00:47:36.347
Fortunately there's
more than one bathroom


774
00:47:36.415 --> 00:47:37.348
In this house.

775
00:47:37.416 --> 00:47:40.318
Ain't that much dirt
in all Louisiana.


776
00:47:40.386 --> 00:47:42.621
Get out
of the damn tub!


777
00:47:42.688 --> 00:47:44.556
You watch your
language, young lady.


778
00:47:44.624 --> 00:47:47.225
Mama keeps stabbing herself
in the kitchen.


779
00:47:47.292 --> 00:47:49.260
Show her your hands, mama.

780
00:47:49.328 --> 00:47:50.729
I think you better hush.

781
00:47:50.796 --> 00:47:52.230
And where's daddy?

782
00:47:52.297 --> 00:47:53.732
He's never home.

783
00:47:53.799 --> 00:47:55.700
He's supposed
to be home sometimes!


784
00:47:55.768 --> 00:47:57.769
Listen,
you little ingrate...


785
00:47:57.837 --> 00:47:59.571
Your father works hard

786
00:47:59.639 --> 00:48:01.573
So we can have a house
with 4 bathrooms.


787
00:48:01.641 --> 00:48:03.274
Not every night,
he's not working!


788
00:48:03.342 --> 00:48:04.208
I know he's not!

789
00:48:07.446 --> 00:48:09.113
I-
-I mean...

790
00:48:09.181 --> 00:48:11.883
Let me borrow you
for a minute.


791
00:48:16.856 --> 00:48:18.189
Poe?

792
00:48:21.794 --> 00:48:24.296
Is that your idea of being
a good daughter?


793
00:48:24.363 --> 00:48:25.830
It's true.

794
00:48:25.898 --> 00:48:27.232
He never comes home,

795
00:48:27.300 --> 00:48:29.000
And it's making her
nervous.


796
00:48:29.068 --> 00:48:31.269
She cuts herself.

797
00:48:31.337 --> 00:48:32.671
Oh, and you're
just being helpful


798
00:48:32.738 --> 00:48:34.573
Bringing it up,
is that it?


799
00:48:34.640 --> 00:48:35.574
She's nervous

800
00:48:35.641 --> 00:48:38.210
'cause he's messing
with other women.


801
00:48:38.277 --> 00:48:41.213
What did you say?

802
00:48:41.280 --> 00:48:43.315
Nothing.

803
00:48:43.382 --> 00:48:44.816
Play games with me,

804
00:48:44.883 --> 00:48:46.484
I swear,
I'll slap you blind.


805
00:48:46.552 --> 00:48:48.420
It's true. I saw them.

806
00:48:48.487 --> 00:48:50.121
