Cisely: Let me go!

1067
01:05:54.211 --> 01:05:56.512
I'm gonna kill her!

1068
01:06:04.772 --> 01:06:07.273
I don't know
what happened.


1069
01:06:07.341 --> 01:06:08.974
It's like
she went crazy.


1070
01:06:09.042 --> 01:06:10.976
We thought she was having
a seizure or something.


1071
01:06:11.044 --> 01:06:12.445
We were so scared.

1072
01:06:12.513 --> 01:06:15.181
Is it my fault
'cause I hit her?


1073
01:06:15.248 --> 01:06:18.418
No, Roz,
it's not your fault.


1074
01:06:18.485 --> 01:06:20.787
Let me look at her.

1075
01:06:20.854 --> 01:06:22.087
Louis...

1076
01:06:24.057 --> 01:06:26.859
She started
her period.


1077
01:06:26.927 --> 01:06:29.161
Did you know that?

1078
01:06:29.229 --> 01:06:30.095
No.

1079
01:06:31.332 --> 01:06:34.434
Roz: She didn't even
tell me.


1080
01:06:53.821 --> 01:06:56.823
Go away, daddy.
I don't want you here.


1081
01:06:56.890 --> 01:06:59.258
I just want
to take your pulse


1082
01:06:59.326 --> 01:07:02.194
And your temperature,
baby. Doctor stuff.


1083
01:07:02.262 --> 01:07:04.029
No!

1084
01:07:04.097 --> 01:07:06.131
I don't want you
looking at me.


1085
01:07:09.570 --> 01:07:13.706
Ok. I know a nice
lady doctor


1086
01:07:13.774 --> 01:07:15.708
We can take you to.

1087
01:07:15.776 --> 01:07:17.276
Would you like that?

1088
01:07:35.929 --> 01:07:38.163
[humming <i>amazing Grace]</i>

1089
01:07:54.632 --> 01:07:57.733
Excuse me. How much
for this pineapple?


1090
01:08:01.872 --> 01:08:04.974
I said, how much
for this pineapple?


1091
01:08:05.042 --> 01:08:07.043
25 cents. You want it?

1092
01:08:07.110 --> 01:08:09.445
That's too much.

1093
01:08:09.513 --> 01:08:11.330
Hey!

1094
01:08:11.398 --> 01:08:13.616
Hey! Get her!

1095
01:08:18.255 --> 01:08:20.356
Bad girl.

1096
01:08:22.459 --> 01:08:24.060
<i>Mechante 'tite.</i>

1097
01:08:26.664 --> 01:08:29.165
Bad girl.

1098
01:08:35.906 --> 01:08:37.707
[Elzora cackling]

1099
01:08:39.042 --> 01:08:40.159
Yes, I can!

1100
01:08:40.227 --> 01:08:41.660
No, you can't. Ha ha!

1101
01:08:41.728 --> 01:08:42.995
Yes, I can!

1102
01:08:43.063 --> 01:08:44.497
No, you can't!

1103
01:08:44.565 --> 01:08:47.166
And I'm gonna be always
be able to beat you,


1104
01:08:47.234 --> 01:08:48.667
'cause you
are a chicken!


1105
01:08:48.735 --> 01:08:50.336
No, I'm not!

1106
01:08:52.840 --> 01:08:53.773
Eve: Cisely!

1107
01:08:53.841 --> 01:08:56.776
She blames me for not
making you happy,


1108
01:08:56.844 --> 01:08:58.711
Or she thinks
I'm driving you away.


1109
01:08:58.779 --> 01:09:00.513
She is a child, Roz.

1110
01:09:00.581 --> 01:09:02.615
Just give her time.

1111
01:09:02.683 --> 01:09:05.885
How much time,
Louis?


1112
01:09:05.953 --> 01:09:09.021
It's already
been 2 weeks.


1113
01:09:09.089 --> 01:09:11.491
She won't...Eat.

1114
01:09:11.558 --> 01:09:13.559
She won't speak.

1115
01:09:15.028 --> 01:09:18.397
It's like
she's sleepwalking.


1116
01:09:22.503 --> 01:09:25.371
Louis: This, um...

1117
01:09:25.438 --> 01:09:28.207
Psychologist fellow
seems to think


1118
01:09:28.274 --> 01:09:30.142
You need kind of a...

1119
01:09:30.210 --> 01:09:32.444
A vacation from us.

1120
01:09:32.513 --> 01:09:35.381
It's just a suggestion.

1121
01:09:35.448 --> 01:09:38.918
We'd never send you away
unless you wanted to go.


1122
01:09:44.024 --> 01:09:46.158
[whispering]
listen...


1123
01:09:46.226 --> 01:09:48.160
Whatever it is,

1124
01:09:48.228 --> 01:09:50.696
We can work it out
together.


1125
01:09:51.899 --> 01:09:54.700
Everything's gonna be
fine again, I promise.


1126
01:09:59.973 --> 01:10:02.207
I want to go.

1127
01:10:02.275 --> 01:10:04.276
What?

1128
01:10:08.214 --> 01:10:11.651
What'd you say,
baby?


1129
01:10:11.718 --> 01:10:14.253
I said, I want to go.

1130
01:10:18.992 --> 01:10:20.927
Well,
it's all settled.


1131
01:10:20.994 --> 01:10:24.964
I talked
to your grandmother,


1132
01:10:25.032 --> 01:10:28.434
And she just can't
wait to see you.


1133
01:10:32.940 --> 01:10:37.176
If you leave me alone
with them, I'll die.


1134
01:10:37.243 --> 01:10:39.745
I'll die, Cisely.

1135
01:10:42.649 --> 01:10:44.650
What's wrong with you?

1136
01:10:44.718 --> 01:10:46.452
Why won't you tell me?

1137
01:10:46.519 --> 01:10:48.487
Is it me?

1138
01:10:48.555 --> 01:10:51.023
Is it something
that I did?


1139
01:10:51.091 --> 01:10:55.427
Why won't you
talk to me?


1140
01:10:58.565 --> 01:11:00.933
Of course it's not you,
rabbit.


1141
01:11:06.039 --> 01:11:08.273
You're my only friend.

1142
01:11:08.341 --> 01:11:09.976
Then...

1143
01:11:10.043 --> 01:11:11.677
What is it?

1144
01:11:11.745 --> 01:11:16.148
Tell me. I promise
I won't tell anybody.


1145
01:11:18.685 --> 01:11:21.921
Do you remember
the Storm?


1146
01:11:21.989 --> 01:11:24.924
The day you cut your
hair and mama hit you?


1147
01:11:28.028 --> 01:11:32.131
Did you hear mama and daddy
fighting that night?


1148
01:11:32.198 --> 01:11:33.298
Yeah.

1149
01:11:35.068 --> 01:11:38.137
Part of it was about me

1150
01:11:38.204 --> 01:11:42.008
And how he let me
visit him that day.


1151
01:11:43.677 --> 01:11:46.545
The other thing
they were fighting about...


1152
01:11:48.181 --> 01:11:50.315
Was Matty Mereaux.

1153
01:11:52.218 --> 01:11:54.954
Mama knows about
daddy and Matty?


1154
01:11:57.024 --> 01:11:58.991
Everybody knows.

1155
01:11:59.059 --> 01:12:00.526
She's been hanging
around his office,


1156
01:12:00.593 --> 01:12:02.294
Right in front
of everyone.


1157
01:12:02.362 --> 01:12:04.797
You believe me now

1158
01:12:04.865 --> 01:12:06.799
About what happened
at the party?


1159
01:12:09.936 --> 01:12:11.804
I believed you then.

1160
01:12:14.107 --> 01:12:15.808
Anyway...

1161
01:12:15.876 --> 01:12:20.612
I waited until I heard
mama go upstairs.


1162
01:12:23.216 --> 01:12:25.184
I went downstairs.

1163
01:12:28.789 --> 01:12:32.124
I was afraid of what
she might have said.


1164
01:12:36.697 --> 01:12:39.865
I was afraid
he would divorce us.


1165
01:12:39.933 --> 01:12:42.001
[thunder]

1166
01:12:46.040 --> 01:12:48.841
I wanted to make him
feel better.


1167
01:12:58.586 --> 01:13:00.787
I sat on his lap.

1168
01:13:02.122 --> 01:13:04.490
And I was scared.

1169
01:13:22.476 --> 01:13:23.977
And I was trying
to get away,


1170
01:13:24.044 --> 01:13:26.913
And he was hugging me
and kissing me...


1171
01:13:26.981 --> 01:13:29.816
Until I finally
pushed him away with my knee.


1172
01:13:29.883 --> 01:13:33.786
I must have hurt him
because he hit me.


1173
01:13:33.854 --> 01:13:36.756
[sobbing]
he's never hit me.


1174
01:13:39.259 --> 01:13:41.393
Baby. Baby, I'm sorry.

1175
01:13:41.461 --> 01:13:44.130
And then I ran.

1176
01:13:46.834 --> 01:13:48.635
I'll kill him,
Cisely.


1177
01:13:48.702 --> 01:13:50.503
I swear it.

1178
01:13:50.570 --> 01:13:53.773
I'll kill him
for hurting you.


1179
01:14:03.751 --> 01:14:05.752
[birds chirping]

1180
01:14:12.726 --> 01:14:15.327
Bye-bye, now.

1181
01:14:15.395 --> 01:14:17.780
Roz: I'll be gone
a week or so.


1182
01:14:17.847 --> 01:14:20.216
I just want to get her
settled in.


1183
01:14:22.719 --> 01:14:25.271
Bye, Poe.
Be good.


1184
01:14:34.748 --> 01:14:37.633
I'm just going
to drop them off.


1185
01:14:37.700 --> 01:14:39.601
Be back before dinner.

1186
01:14:57.554 --> 01:14:59.655
[car starts]

1187
01:15:13.337 --> 01:15:15.171
[door closes]

1188
01:15:28.385 --> 01:15:30.853
Maybe he ran
into traffic.


1189
01:15:30.920 --> 01:15:32.321
It's Sunday.

1190
01:15:37.794 --> 01:15:41.130
He'll be back
and so will Cisely.


1191
01:15:41.198 --> 01:15:43.899
I know she will.

1192
01:15:43.967 --> 01:15:47.103
Life is filled
with good-byes, Eve--


1193
01:15:47.170 --> 01:15:48.637
A million good-byes--

1194
01:15:48.705 --> 01:15:51.507
And it hurts every time.

1195
01:15:52.675 --> 01:15:56.078
Sometimes I feel like
I've lost so much,


1196
01:15:56.146 --> 01:15:59.581
I have to find
new things to lose.


1197
01:15:59.649 --> 01:16:03.785
All I know is there must be
a divine point to it all,


1198
01:16:03.853 --> 01:16:06.288
And it's just over my head.

1199
01:16:06.356 --> 01:16:11.193
Then, when we die,
it will all come clear,


1200
01:16:11.261 --> 01:16:12.828
And we'll say...

1201
01:16:12.896 --> 01:16:16.532
"so that was
the damn point."


1202
01:16:16.599 --> 01:16:20.569
And sometimes I think
there's no point at all,


1203
01:16:20.637 --> 01:16:23.172
And that's the point.

1204
01:16:23.240 --> 01:16:26.509
All I know is
most people's lives


1205
01:16:26.576 --> 01:16:29.278
Are a great disappointment
to them.


1206
01:16:29.346 --> 01:16:31.713
And no one leaves
this earth


1207
01:16:31.781 --> 01:16:34.850
Without feeling
terrible pain.


1208
01:16:34.918 --> 01:16:37.853
And if there is
no divine explanation


1209
01:16:37.921 --> 01:16:40.156
At the end of it all,
well...


1210
01:16:41.925 --> 01:16:44.360
That's sad.

1211
01:16:46.963 --> 01:16:50.066
How do you kill someone
with voodoo?


1212
01:16:51.601 --> 01:16:52.834
[laughs]

1213
01:16:52.902 --> 01:16:55.604
I almost forgot
you was there.


1214
01:16:57.140 --> 01:17:00.076
I mean, do you just
wish real hard


1215
01:17:00.143 --> 01:17:01.643
That they were dead,

1216
01:17:01.711 --> 01:17:03.879
Or do you have to do
something special?


1217
01:17:03.947 --> 01:17:07.583
I suppose you put some
of their hair on a doll


1218
01:17:07.650 --> 01:17:09.318
And stick pins in it
or something.


1219
01:17:09.386 --> 01:17:11.253
I really don't know.

1220
01:17:11.321 --> 01:17:14.723
What makes you ask
a thing like that?


1221
01:17:14.791 --> 01:17:15.757
Nothing.

1222
01:17:15.825 --> 01:17:18.894
Well, you must have been
thinking something


1223
01:17:18.962 --> 01:17:21.330
Right before
you were thinking that.


1224
01:17:21.398 --> 01:17:24.266
What led you to that
particular thought?


1225
01:17:25.502 --> 01:17:27.970
I don't know.

1226
01:17:29.372 --> 01:17:33.809
Is there someone around here
that you're angry with?


1227
01:17:33.876 --> 01:17:36.678
Someone
that you want dead?


1228
01:17:38.315 --> 01:17:39.781
I'm going inside.

1229
01:17:39.849 --> 01:17:44.019
No. I think you better
tell me what's on your mind.


1230
01:17:44.087 --> 01:17:47.490
You have 5 seconds.

1231
01:17:51.027 --> 01:17:53.496
Give me your hands.

1232
01:17:56.199 --> 01:17:58.601
Give them to me.

1233
01:18:12.115 --> 01:18:14.683
Well, go on and keep secrets
if you want to.


1234
01:18:14.751 --> 01:18:16.619
I won't squeeze it
out of you.


1235
01:18:16.686 --> 01:18:20.356
But you can't kill people
with voodoo.


1236
01:18:20.423 --> 01:18:21.524
That's ridiculous.

1237
01:18:27.197 --> 01:18:28.864
[door slams]

1238
01:19:26.356 --> 01:19:27.356
Hey, red.

1239
01:19:27.423 --> 01:19:30.009
Hah. Didn't mean
to startle you, baby.


1240
01:19:30.077 --> 01:19:31.510
Hi, Mr. Mereaux.

1241
01:19:31.578 --> 01:19:33.512
Hi. How's your family?

1242
01:19:33.580 --> 01:19:35.680
Everybody's fine.

1243
01:19:35.748 --> 01:19:37.816
How's Matty?

1244
01:19:38.118 --> 01:19:39.235
Hey, same as always.

1245
01:19:39.302 --> 01:19:42.254
You know,
salty and sweet.


1246
01:19:42.322 --> 01:19:43.805
What you looking for?

1247
01:19:43.874 --> 01:19:46.025
Um...Apples.

1248
01:19:46.093 --> 01:19:47.360
Apples.

1249
01:19:47.427 --> 01:19:50.796
Well, you know, you just
walked right past them.


1250
01:19:54.667 --> 01:19:57.052
Oh. Thanks.

1251
01:19:58.187 --> 01:19:59.888
Lord have mercy.

1252
01:20:09.215 --> 01:20:10.849
Mr. Mereaux?

1253
01:20:10.916 --> 01:20:12.917
Yes, Eve?

1254
01:20:15.355 --> 01:20:17.156
You still teachin'?

1255
01:20:17.223 --> 01:20:18.490
Sure, darling.

1256
01:20:18.558 --> 01:20:20.892
Down at Xavier,
New Orleans.


1257
01:20:20.960 --> 01:20:22.361
Been there for years.

1258
01:20:22.428 --> 01:20:24.363
That's a long drive.

1259
01:20:24.430 --> 01:20:25.497
Yeah.

1260
01:20:25.565 --> 01:20:27.499
Well, you know, sometimes,
if the weather's bad,


1261
01:20:27.567 --> 01:20:29.168
I just stay on campus.

1262
01:20:29.235 --> 01:20:30.969
But usually, you know,
I try to get home


1263
01:20:31.037 --> 01:20:33.738
So Matty don't get
too lonely.


1264
01:20:33.806 --> 01:20:36.741
Matty don't seem like
the lonely type.


1265
01:20:36.809 --> 01:20:38.877
Nah.

1266
01:20:38.944 --> 01:20:40.779
Nah, I guess not.

1267
01:20:40.846 --> 01:20:43.182
You must get home
real late...


1268
01:20:43.249 --> 01:20:45.450
Well,
when you get home.


1269
01:20:45.518 --> 01:20:47.519
Sometimes.

1270
01:20:47.587 --> 01:20:49.254
So does my daddy.

1271
01:20:49.322 --> 01:20:50.755
Every night.

1272
01:20:50.823 --> 01:20:53.091
My mama gets
real lonely.


1273
01:20:53.159 --> 01:20:56.094
But then,
she's the lonely type.


1274
01:20:57.597 --> 01:20:59.931
Not like daddy
and Matty.


1275
01:21:02.569 --> 01:21:05.170
Well...

1276
01:21:05.238 --> 01:21:06.605
Bye.

1277
01:21:19.268 --> 01:21:20.769
Eve: Excuse me.

1278
01:21:29.762 --> 01:21:31.597
<i>Mechante</i>
<i>'tite fille.</i>


1279
01:21:32.798 --> 01:21:35.400
I remember you,
pineapple thief.


1280
01:21:38.804 --> 01:21:41.673
Um...Hi.

1281
01:21:41.741 --> 01:21:44.610
I've been looking
for you.


1282
01:21:44.677 --> 01:21:47.412
Only people ever look
for me got good reason.


1283
01:21:47.480 --> 01:21:48.714
I got good reason.

1284
01:21:48.781 --> 01:21:50.215
You got money?

1285
01:21:50.283 --> 01:21:52.050
$20.

1286
01:21:52.118 --> 01:21:54.553
20?!

1287
01:21:54.621 --> 01:21:55.887
Let me see.

1288
01:21:59.091 --> 01:22:00.259
Give me.

1289
01:22:06.500 --> 01:22:08.667
Wh-where
are we going?


1290
01:22:08.735 --> 01:22:10.102
My office.

1291
01:22:54.381 --> 01:22:57.949
Are you related
to Mozelle Batiste?


1292
01:22:58.017 --> 01:23:00.018
I'm her niece.

1293
01:23:00.086 --> 01:23:01.820
And she's the one
you want dead.


1294
01:23:01.888 --> 01:23:03.822
No. Someone else.

1295
01:23:03.890 --> 01:23:06.024
Hmm. Too bad.

1296
01:23:06.092 --> 01:23:09.928
<i>Tant pis.</i> Why you want
this person dead?


1297
01:23:09.996 --> 01:23:11.063
<i>Quo fais?</i>

1298
01:23:11.130 --> 01:23:12.998
<i>Raisons prive.</i>

1299
01:23:13.066 --> 01:23:16.302
This person...Harm you?

1300
01:23:17.437 --> 01:23:19.171
Others in my family.

1301
01:23:21.608 --> 01:23:22.841
I will give you something

1302
01:23:22.909 --> 01:23:25.177
To protect you and your family
from this person.


1303
01:23:25.245 --> 01:23:27.012
I want him dead!

1304
01:23:27.080 --> 01:23:28.380
<i>M'ole li mort!</i>

1305
01:23:30.684 --> 01:23:33.352
For certain.
You are sure.


1306
01:23:34.521 --> 01:23:36.689
Yes, ma'am.

1307
01:23:36.756 --> 01:23:40.926
People have a way of dying
at their own speed.


1308
01:23:40.993 --> 01:23:43.562
But I will see
what I can do.


1309
01:23:44.997 --> 01:23:46.932
I will need some hair

1310
01:23:46.999 --> 01:23:49.335
From the head
of this person.


1311
01:23:49.402 --> 01:23:52.904
I brought you some
from a comb.


1312
01:23:52.972 --> 01:23:54.740
I hope it's enough,
though.


1313
01:23:54.807 --> 01:23:56.208
Well...

1314
01:23:56.276 --> 01:23:57.876
<i>Eh, bien.</i>

1315
01:23:57.944 --> 01:24:00.646
But don't be too eager.

1316
01:24:00.714 --> 01:24:02.914
You come back
Thursday night.


1317
01:24:02.982 --> 01:24:05.884
And we will see.

1318
01:24:05.952 --> 01:24:07.519
We'll see.

1319
01:25:48.253 --> 01:25:50.421
Get the hell
off my property


1320
01:25:50.490 --> 01:25:52.123
Before I cook you
and eat you!


1321
01:25:57.763 --> 01:26:00.298
Is that you,
pineapple thief?


1322
01:26:03.469 --> 01:26:04.335
Come.

1323
01:26:17.750 --> 01:26:19.250
Mmm hmm...

